{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "wfm-backend-collection",
    "name": "WFM Backend API",
    "description": "Work Force Management Backend API — Spec 002 (Clean Architecture / NestJS 11)\n\n**Base URL:** `http://localhost:3001/api`\n\n**Start stack:** `npm run docker:dev`\n**Seed data:** `npm run db:seed`\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nHTTP → Controller → Use Case → Domain Policy → Repository (Prisma)\n```\n\nBusiness rules live in **use cases** and **domain policies** (`user-management.policy.ts`). Controllers only handle HTTP; repositories only handle persistence.\n\n---\n\n## User roles\n\n| Role | Code | Office | Created via API |\n|------|------|--------|-----------------|\n| Senior Manager E&S | `SENIOR_MANAGER_ES` | — | Seed only |\n| RA Environment (HO) | `RA_ENVIRONMENT_HO` | `HEAD_OFFICE` | Yes |\n| RA E&S (Tehsil) | `RA_ES_TEHSIL` | `TEHSIL_OFFICE` | Seed only (1 per tehsil) |\n| World Bank User | `WORLD_BANK_USER` | `WORLD_BANK_OFFICE` | Yes |\n\n## Senior Manager permissions\n\n- **Create:** `RA_ENVIRONMENT_HO`, `WORLD_BANK_USER` (must assign matching office)\n- **Activate / deactivate:** all roles including seeded tehsil RAs\n- **Edit / delete / reset credentials:** `RA_ENVIRONMENT_HO`, `WORLD_BANK_USER` only\n- **Cannot:** create or delete `RA_ES_TEHSIL`, change user roles, delete self\n- **View:** audit logs, offices, users\n\n## Authenticated (non-admin) access\n\n`RA_ES_TEHSIL`, `RA_ENVIRONMENT_HO`, `WORLD_BANK_USER` can access:\n- `GET /auth/profile`\n- `GET /tehsils` and `GET /tehsils/:id/villages`\n\nAll `/users`, `/offices`, `/audit-logs` routes require `SENIOR_MANAGER_ES`.\n\n---\n\n## Seed credentials\n\n| Account | Email | Password |\n|---------|-------|----------|\n| Senior Manager | `senior.manager@wfm.local` | `SeniorManager@123` |\n| RA E&S (Ahmadpur Sial) | `ra.es.ahmadpur-sial@wfm.local` | `RaEs@123` |\n\n---\n\n## Suggested flow\n\n1. **Health Check** — verify API is up\n2. **Login (Senior Manager)** — saves `token`, `actorId`, `actorRole`\n3. **List All Offices** — saves `headOfficeId`, `worldBankOfficeId`, `tehsilOfficeId`\n4. **Create RA Environment (HO)** — saves `userId`\n5. **Create World Bank User** — saves `worldBankUserId`\n6. **List Users** — saves `raEsUserId` (first seeded tehsil RA)\n7. **List Tehsils** → **List Villages by Tehsil**\n8. **List Audit Logs** — paginated trail of user mutations\n\n> **Note:** Workforce scheduling is not implemented yet. This collection covers auth, RBAC, offices, geography, and audit logging only.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3001/api" },
    { "key": "token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "actorId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "actorRole", "value": "" },
    { "key": "userId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "worldBankUserId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "raEsUserId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "temporaryPassword", "value": "" },
    { "key": "headOfficeId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "worldBankOfficeId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "tehsilId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "tehsilOfficeId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "villageId", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Returns status ok', () => pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('ok'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Public — no auth required.\n\n**Response:** `{ \"status\": \"ok\" }`"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (Senior Manager)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Returns accessToken and user', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(res.accessToken).to.be.a('string');",
                  "  pm.expect(res.user.role).to.eql('SENIOR_MANAGER_ES');",
                  "});",
                  "if (res.accessToken) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', res.accessToken);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('token', res.accessToken);",
                  "}",
                  "if (res.user) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('actorId', res.user.id);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('actorRole', res.user.role);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('actorId', res.user.id);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('actorRole', res.user.role);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"senior.manager@wfm.local\",\n  \"password\": \"SeniorManager@123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Senior Manager E&S — full admin access to users, offices, and audit logs.\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"accessToken\": \"<jwt>\",\n  \"user\": { \"id\", \"email\", \"username\", \"role\", \"createdAt\" }\n}\n```\n\nInactive accounts return `401`. Invalid credentials return generic `401` (no user enumeration)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (RA E&S — Ahmadpur Sial)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Role is RA_ES_TEHSIL', () => pm.expect(res.user.role).to.eql('RA_ES_TEHSIL'));",
                  "if (res.accessToken) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', res.accessToken);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('token', res.accessToken);",
                  "}",
                  "if (res.user) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('actorId', res.user.id);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('actorRole', res.user.role);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('actorId', res.user.id);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('actorRole', res.user.role);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"ra.es.ahmadpur-sial@wfm.local\",\n  \"password\": \"RaEs@123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Seeded tehsil RA — can access profile and tehsil geography only. Cannot manage users, offices, or audit logs.\n\nEmail pattern: `ra.es.<tehsil-slug>@wfm.local`"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Profile",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const user = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Returns authenticated user', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(user).to.have.property('id');",
                  "  pm.expect(user).to.have.property('email');",
                  "  pm.expect(user).to.have.property('username');",
                  "  pm.expect(user).to.have.property('role');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/profile",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "profile"]
            },
            "description": "Any authenticated user. JWT is re-validated on every request; inactive users are rejected even with a valid token.\n\n**Response:** `{ id, email, username, role }`"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Offices",
      "description": "Senior Manager only. Read-only listing for office assignment when creating users.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List All Offices",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const offices = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Returns office array', () => pm.expect(offices).to.be.an('array'));",
                  "const ho = offices.find(o => o.type === 'HEAD_OFFICE');",
                  "const wb = offices.find(o => o.type === 'WORLD_BANK_OFFICE');",
                  "const tehsilOffice = offices.find(o => o.type === 'TEHSIL_OFFICE');",
                  "if (ho) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('headOfficeId', ho.id);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('headOfficeId', ho.id);",
                  "}",
                  "if (wb) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('worldBankOfficeId', wb.id);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('worldBankOfficeId', wb.id);",
                  "}",
                  "if (tehsilOffice) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('tehsilOfficeId', tehsilOffice.id);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('tehsilOfficeId', tehsilOffice.id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/offices",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["offices"]
            },
            "description": "Returns Head Office (1), World Bank Office (1), and Tehsil Offices (16).\n\n**Response item:** `{ id, type, name, tehsilId, tehsilName, createdAt, updatedAt }`"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Head Offices",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const offices = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('All offices are HEAD_OFFICE', () => {",
                  "  offices.forEach(o => pm.expect(o.type).to.eql('HEAD_OFFICE'));",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/offices?type=HEAD_OFFICE",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["offices"],
              "query": [{ "key": "type", "value": "HEAD_OFFICE" }]
            },
            "description": "Filter by `HEAD_OFFICE`. Required office type for `RA_ENVIRONMENT_HO` users."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List World Bank Offices",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const offices = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('All offices are WORLD_BANK_OFFICE', () => {",
                  "  offices.forEach(o => pm.expect(o.type).to.eql('WORLD_BANK_OFFICE'));",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/offices?type=WORLD_BANK_OFFICE",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["offices"],
              "query": [{ "key": "type", "value": "WORLD_BANK_OFFICE" }]
            },
            "description": "Filter by `WORLD_BANK_OFFICE`. Required office type for `WORLD_BANK_USER` users."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Tehsil Offices",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const offices = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('All offices are TEHSIL_OFFICE', () => {",
                  "  offices.forEach(o => pm.expect(o.type).to.eql('TEHSIL_OFFICE'));",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/offices?type=TEHSIL_OFFICE",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["offices"],
              "query": [{ "key": "type", "value": "TEHSIL_OFFICE" }]
            },
            "description": "Filter by `TEHSIL_OFFICE`. One per tehsil; each has exactly one seeded `RA_ES_TEHSIL` user. Tehsil offices are not assignable via the create-user API."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Users",
      "description": "Senior Manager only. All mutating actions are recorded in audit logs.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Users",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const users = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Returns user array', () => pm.expect(users).to.be.an('array'));",
                  "const raEnv = users.find(u => u.role === 'RA_ENVIRONMENT_HO');",
                  "const raEs = users.find(u => u.role === 'RA_ES_TEHSIL');",
                  "const wb = users.find(u => u.role === 'WORLD_BANK_USER');",
                  "if (raEnv) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', raEnv.id);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('userId', raEnv.id);",
                  "}",
                  "if (raEs) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('raEsUserId', raEs.id);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('raEsUserId', raEs.id);",
                  "}",
                  "if (wb) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('worldBankUserId', wb.id);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('worldBankUserId', wb.id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/users",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["users"]
            },
            "description": "Lists all users. Saves first `RA_ENVIRONMENT_HO` → `userId`, first `RA_ES_TEHSIL` → `raEsUserId`, first `WORLD_BANK_USER` → `worldBankUserId`.\n\n**Response item:** `{ id, email, username, role, status, officeId, officeName, officeType, tehsilName, createdById, createdAt, updatedAt }`"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const user = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Returns user with id', () => pm.expect(user.id).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('userId')));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["users", "{{userId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Get a single user by ID. Uses `userId` from List Users or Create requests."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create RA Environment (HO)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('User created with correct role and office', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(res.role).to.eql('RA_ENVIRONMENT_HO');",
                  "  pm.expect(res.officeType).to.eql('HEAD_OFFICE');",
                  "  pm.expect(res.status).to.eql('ACTIVE');",
                  "});",
                  "if (res.id) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', res.id);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('userId', res.id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"ra.env@wfm.local\",\n  \"username\": \"ra_env_ho\",\n  \"password\": \"Research@123\",\n  \"role\": \"RA_ENVIRONMENT_HO\",\n  \"officeId\": \"{{headOfficeId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/users",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["users"]
            },
            "description": "Creates `RA_ENVIRONMENT_HO` assigned to Head Office.\n\n**Business rules enforced:**\n- Only Senior Manager can create\n- `officeId` required and must be `HEAD_OFFICE`\n- Email and username must be unique\n- Password hashed with bcrypt (never returned)\n- Writes `USER_CREATED` audit log\n\nRun **List All Offices** first to populate `headOfficeId`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create World Bank User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('User created with correct role and office', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(res.role).to.eql('WORLD_BANK_USER');",
                  "  pm.expect(res.officeType).to.eql('WORLD_BANK_OFFICE');",
                  "});",
                  "if (res.id) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('worldBankUserId', res.id);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('worldBankUserId', res.id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"worldbank@wfm.local\",\n  \"username\": \"wb_user\",\n  \"password\": \"WorldBank@123\",\n  \"role\": \"WORLD_BANK_USER\",\n  \"officeId\": \"{{worldBankOfficeId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/users",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["users"]
            },
            "description": "Creates `WORLD_BANK_USER` assigned to World Bank Office.\n\n`RA_ES_TEHSIL` and `SENIOR_MANAGER_ES` cannot be created via API (returns `403`).\n\nRun **List All Offices** first to populate `worldBankOfficeId`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const user = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Username updated', () => pm.expect(user.username).to.eql('ra_env_ho_updated'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"ra_env_ho_updated\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["users", "{{userId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Update `email`, `username`, or `officeId`. **Role cannot be changed** (`403`). If changing `officeId`, the new office must match the user's role type.\n\nWrites `USER_UPDATED` audit log."
          }
        },
